    "content_hash": "d70b4effd245215d",
    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "FINANCE \u0026 STRATEGY INTERN (FINANCIAL PLANNING \u0026 ANALYSIS)\n\nJoin us in our mission to transform the way people shop and eat, where impact, innovation, and growth drives everything we do. Our Finance team shapes the company's future by directing capital to high-impact investments, developing robust financial strategies, and ensuring we deliver long-term value while pursuing our ambitious mission.\n\nWe’re looking for a Finance \u0026 Strategy Intern to join our Paris team. In this role, you’ll help us drive effective decision-making through rigorous financial analysis and support the long-term value creation of Deliveroo France.\n\nGet to know our Finance https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/the-finance-team/ team — what drives us, how we work, and what you can expect.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BE DOING\n\nYou’ll be joining the France Finance and Strategy team. We are a dynamic group focused on facilitating world-class execution, sharing business drivers, and managing risks while uncovering new opportunities in a fast-evolving market.\n\nHere’s what your day-to-day might look like:\n\n - Drive Financial Performance: Support the tracking and analysis of financial performance against reforecasts and annual targets, with a specific focus on marketing spend.\n\n - Collaborate on Forecasting: Partner with business teams on the monthly reforecast process to ensure absolute exhaustivity and accuracy.\n\n - Ensure Financial Integrity: Participate in month-end processes to ensure the accuracy of financial accounts and assist in preparing analysis for senior management.\n\n - Optimise Operations: Continuously collaborate with the wider team to improve efficiency by building new analytical tools and streamlining processes.\n\n - Deliver Ad-hoc Insights: Execute deep-dive projects and bespoke financial analysis based on evolving business needs and market trends.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL NEED TO THRIVE\n\nEssential:\n\n - Analytical Rigour: Advanced Excel skills and a proven ability to work quickly and accurately under tight deadlines.\n\n - Communication Skills: Excellent interpersonal and presentation skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively as a team player.\n\n - Language Proficiency: Fluent and comfortable working professionally in both French and English.\n\n - Stakeholder Management: Proven ability to support complex projects involving multiple stakeholders across different functions.\n\n - Academic Background: Currently pursuing a Master’s or Bachelor’s degree with a foundational understanding of the financial sector.\n\nNice to Have:\n\n - Technical Tools: Knowledge of SQL or experience with data visualisation tools.\n\n - Field Curiosity: A willingness to go into the field to transform real-world observations into data-backed hypotheses.\n\n\nWHY JOIN US?\n\nAt Deliveroo, you’ll do work that matters, solving real-world problems in a three-sided marketplace that’s constantly evolving. We’re food lovers, problem solvers, community builders and more, brought together by a shared drive to make things better. Working here you can expect to:\n\n🔧 Make a visible impact every day\n\nYour work directly improves experiences for customers, partners and riders.\n\n🌱 Learn fast in an entrepreneurial environment\n\nWork close to the market with autonomy, pace and real responsibility.\n\n🧠 Build a career, not just a role\n\nStretch yourself, develop new skills and grow as the business evolves.\n\n🌎 Deliver together in an inclusive culture\n\nCollaborative, values-driven teams that support how you work best.\n\nWe aim to create a fair process that lets your skills shine—our interview typically includes 3-4 stages. Find more about how we hire here https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/how-we-hire/.\n\n\nOUR GLOBAL STRUCTURE\n\nDeliveroo is now part of DoorDash, bringing together teams with even greater reach, scale, and ambition. Depending on your role, you may collaborate with teammates, systems, and leaders across DoorDash and Wolt. Together, we’re unlocking new possibilities as one global team.\n\n\nDIVERSITY, EQUITY AND INCLUSION\n\nAt Deliveroo, we know that a great workplace reflects the world around us and that true diversity and inclusion make us stronger, more creative, and better at what we do. We’re committed to fostering an environment where everyone can do their best work and feel they belong.\n\nWe believe in equality of opportunity and welcome candidates from all backgrounds regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, socio-economic background, religion, or belief.\n\nIf you have a disability or long-term health condition and need support to apply for one of our roles, or require any reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, you’ll have the opportunity to let us know once you’ve submitted your application.\n\nIf you’re excited about making a real impact in a fast-moving marketplace and growing your career alongside ambitious, supportive teams, we’d love to hear from you!",
